    public interface Writeable
    Generalized description of a "type" that maps a domain type to one or more JDBC types. Defines a 2-phase process for writing values: * unresolve(java.lang.Object, org.hibernate.engine.spi.SharedSessionContractImplementor) - Transforms the domain representation of value of this type into its "hydrated array" representation. The exact outcome of this depends on the nature of this type (basic, embedded, etc). Named as a corollary to Readable.resolveHydratedState(java.lang.Object, org.hibernate.sql.exec.spi.ExecutionContext, org.hibernate.engine.spi.SharedSessionContractImplementor, java.lang.Object). * dehydrate(java.lang.Object, org.hibernate.metamodel.model.domain.spi.Writeable.JdbcValueCollector, org.hibernate.sql.ast.Clause, org.hibernate.engine.spi.SharedSessionContractImplementor) - Transforms each value in the "hydrated" array into a call to the supplied Writeable.JdbcValueCollector
    See Also:
